Write a PHP script to remove all characters from a string except a-z A-Z 0-9 or " " using an array.

CODE:
<?php
// Original string with special characters
$text = "Hello@# World! 123 $$ PHP_8.0 is great!!";

// Step 1: Split string into array of characters
$chars = str_split($text);

// Step 2: Filter only allowed characters [a-zA-Z0-9 ]
$filtered = array_filter($chars, function($ch) {
    return preg_match("/[a-zA-Z0-9 ]/", $ch);
});

// Step 3: Join array back into string
$result = implode("", $filtered);

// Display result
echo "Original: $text <br>";
echo "Filtered: $result";
?>

OUTPUT:
Original: Hello@# World! 123 $$ PHP_8.0 is great!! 
Filtered: Hello World 123  PHP80 is great
